4:
O great snake. Servants of scorn.
The time of awakening has arrived!
6:
Answer our desires and be
summoned once again to spread
darkness and chaos!
13:
Murakumo! That mirror has to be a
sacred relic!
16:
Indeed, there is no doubt about it.
We are cut from the same cloth.
19:
Yakumo! You dare stand in our way
once more?!
26:
I am not here for you. I am here for
HER.
29: You are fools to think you have won!
31:
O sacred mirror, unleash your
reflection!
34:
This bodes ill! We should move
before it manifests!
42: I recognize you. You are her...
47:
Manoka, spirit of the mirror, at your
service.
50:
A pleasure to meet your
acquaintance. Are you the ones who
called upon me?
53: ...Why do you look at me so?
64:
Oh. And now your expression has
relaxed. How curious.
72:
You are Ama-no-Murakumo? You
have changed much since last we
met.
77:
It has been a while,
Mafutsu-no-Kagami. If we are
discussing appearances, I believe
yours is the most surprising.
80:
You were called upon as Orochi, and
yet... You have not emerged as such.
84:
I am a mirror. I reflect only the
wishes of my master.
86:
None of those humans claim
lordship over me. As you well know,
all our masters are long gone.
94:
The memories remain, for all the
good that they serve.
97:
They have left me with no purpose.
No reason for being.
103:
How could I forget... The way our
masters' faces contorted with
malice...
106:
The fear. The sealing. The
destruction of all.
109:
Such became my entire reason for
existence.
113:
...A vengeful spirit, to be sure, but
you claim you have lost your
purpose.
117:
As someone severed me from the
resentment our masters left behind.
120:
I do not remember who. I only know
that everything inside me was
released.
128:
After that, I remained in darkness, as
if trapped in slumber.
131:
I have lost my purpose for being. I
am without guidance or a goal.
135:
...Surely you are more than an
empty shell.
138: Is there truly nothing you desire?
145:
After all, I am a mirror. I but reflect
the desires of my master.
149:
I am the one who severed the
hatred from you.
152:
If your only purpose is to fulfill the
wishes of your master...
155:
Then why did you smile when I drove
my blade through you?
159:
If I remembered the reason, would
that expression of yours change?
167:
Manoka, I believe I have come to
understand your situation. What do
you think of traveling with us for a
time?
170:
A lovely idea. In fact, it would save
me much trouble if you agreed.
173:
I'd rather the shogunate remained
unaware of her whereabouts,
especially if she possesses
memories of the past.
177:
...Does that mean the one who
sealed away Murakumo and
Manoka's masters was...
181:
Exactly. Which is why the less you
know, the better.
186:
I suppose I should refrain from
saying more.
191:
You can leave the rest to Alk and I.
Assuming you are fine with this, of
course.
196: Yeah, that's probably for the best.
203: Oh, my. What a beautiful place.
208:
You must be Manoka! Nice to meet
you! I am Inaho!
212:
Could you be the long-awaited lady
of our friend there? My, my!
221:
Thank you for the warm greeting. I
shall be in your care from now on.
231:
A nice place to call home, is it not?
Here you can take as much time as
you need to decide your way of life
moving forward.
235: ...I am to decide my own path?
239:
But of course. We chose our own, did
we not, Yakumo?
244:
I... am fine with whatever path that
allows you to keep smiling.
249: Oho? Now that is a high bar!
253:
My own path... But what would that
entail?
